The paper discusses error-control codes for communication channels, which falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Communications (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The focus on low-complexity devices suggests a possible fit with the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The mention of ubiquitous computing and sensor networks suggests a possible fit with the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the use of feedbacks in the proposed coding schemes suggests a possible fit with the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category.
